abstract = {Construction 4.0 is a revolutionary paradigm that leverages the power of artificial intelligence to facilitate the smart interaction between cyber-physical systems and digital ecosystems for cost and time savings, in addition to improving sustainability. Many techniques and technological advancements in this area have been used to develop frameworks for transforming construction assets into digital building information models that capture the assets' physical properties, possibly in real time, for facility and operations management. Utilizing different technologies, such as 3D laser scanning and unmanned aerial vehicle imaging, these frameworks strive to reduce cost and delivery time through process automation and intelligence. In this chapter, we highlight and analyze these key technologies and describe the techniques and applications enabled by each one. As a case study, we summarize key AI techniques used for object detection and fault identification based on a dataset collected by drones at a site in Qatar. We then propose a new deep learning technique based on convolutional neural networks for fault detection and identification based on digital models and compare its accuracy with the state-of-the-art. Our results show high accuracy in detecting on-site challenges and issues.}
